  "prompt": "How can I use the Wi-Fi on my windows phone (wp8.1) in BHU (hostels, departments, library)?",
  "response": "Using Wi-Fi on a Windows Phone running WP8.1 in BHU (Banaras Hindu University) requires several steps, which may involve configuring your device and obtaining necessary credentials. Here's a general guide to connect to Wi-Fi in BHU hostels, departments, and library:\n\n1. **Obtain Credentials:**\n   - Make sure you have the necessary login credentials (username and password) for the Wi-Fi network. These can usually be obtained from the IT department of BHU or, in the case of hostels, from the hostel office.\n\n2. **Turn on Wi-Fi:**\n   - Open the Settings app on your Windows Phone.\n   - Tap on \"Wi-Fi\" to open Wi-Fi settings.\n   - Ensure the Wi-Fi toggle is turned on.\n\n3. **Connect to the BHU Network:**\n   - Your phone will start scanning for available Wi-Fi networks. Once the network list is populated, select the appropriate BHU network from the list (e.g., BHU_Hostel, BHU_Department, BHU_Library, etc.).\n\n4. **Enter Credentials:**\n   - If the network requires authentication, a login page might pop up asking for a username and password.\n   - Enter your credentials and tap \"Connect.\"\n\n5. **Troubleshooting:**\n   - If you experience issues, ensure you have entered the correct credentials. Sometimes, campus networks require additional configuration, such as setting up a proxy server or installing security certificates.\n   - Contact BHU's IT support for assistance if you cannot connect. They can provide detailed instructions and help configure your device properly.\n\n6. **Additional Configuration (if needed):**\n   - Some educational institutions require additional setup, such as configuring EAP (Extensible Authentication Protocol) settings. If BHU's network uses WPA2-Enterprise, you might need to enter additional parameters like the domain or server verification settings.\n   - Follow any specific guidelines provided by BHU\u2019s IT department for configuring these settings on your Windows Phone.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to connect to the Wi-Fi network in BHU\u2019s hostels, departments, and library. If you have any special instructions from BHU\u2019s IT team, make sure to follow those carefully.",
